<doc id="399064" wikidata="Q282113" url="?curid=399064" title="43 (number)">
<text>43 (forty-three) is the natural number following 42 and preceding 44.

== Mathematics ==
43 is a prime number, and a twin prime of 41, with which it comprises a twin prime. 43 is the smallest prime that is not a Chen prime. 43 is also a Wagstaff prime, and a Heegner number. 43 is the fourth term of Sylvester&#x27;s sequence. 

43 is the largest prime which divides the order of the Janko group J4.

==Notes==
